🔹 1️⃣ IdentityRequest kya hai?
👉 IdentityRequest = user ka access request object
Matlab:-
Jab koi user access maangta hai (role, entitlement, account)
Ya koi admin kisi user ke liye access request create karta hai
➡ Wo sab ek IdentityRequest object me store hota hai.

🔹 2️⃣ Kya ye DB me store hota hai?
✅ Haan bhai, 100% database me store hota hai
Kyun?
Audit ke liye (kisne kya request kiya)
Tracking ke liye (pending / approved / rejected)
Compliance ke liye

📦 DB me ye info hoti hai:-
Kisne request kiya
Kiske liye request hai
Kya request hai (role / access)
Status kya hai

🔹 3️⃣ Ye kya karta hai?
👉 Ye pura access request lifecycle manage karta hai
Flow:-
User ne request ki
System ne IdentityRequest object banaya
Approval process start hua
Manager/Admin approve ya reject karta hai
Provisioning system me access apply hota hai.

🔹 4️⃣ IdentityRequest ke andar kya hota hai (Fields)?
Bhai ye sab important cheeze hoti hain 👇
Field	               Meaning
id:---------------Unique request ID
requestor:--------Kisne request kiya
targetIdentity:---Kiske liye request hai
requestedItems:---Kya access maanga gaya (role / entitlement)
status:-----------Pending / Approved / Rejected
createdDate:------Kab request bani
completedDate:----Kab complete hui
approvalSet:------Approval ka flow (manager / admin)
comments:---------Notes ya justification
priority:---------High/Medium/Low

🔥 1️⃣ Basic Methods (ID / Name / Type):-
Method	                 Kya karta hai
getId():------------Request ka unique ID deta hai
setId(String id):---ID set karta hai
getName():----------Request ka naam deta hai
setName(String name):----Request ka naam set karta hai
getType():----------Request ka type (Access / Role / etc.)
setType(String type):------Type set karta hai

🔥 2️⃣ Request Info Methods:-
Method	                            Kya karta hai
getRequestor():--------------------Kisne request ki
setRequestor(String requestor):----Requestor set karta hai
getTargetIdentity():---------------Kiske liye request hai
setTargetIdentity(String identity):----Target identity set karta hai

🔥 3️⃣ Status Methods:-
Method	                                  Kya karta hai
getStatus():----------------Current status (Pending / Approved / Rejected)
setStatus(String status):---Status set karta hai
isCompleted():--------------Check karta hai complete hua ya nahi
setCompleted(boolean completed):----------Completion flag set karta hai

🔥 4️⃣ Requested Items Methods:-
Method	                              Kya karta hai
getRequestedItems():------------Requested access items list deta hai
setRequestedItems(List items):--Items set karta hai
addRequestedItem(Object item):--Ek item add karta hai

🔥 5️⃣ Approval Methods:-
Method	                                          Kya karta hai
getApprovalSet():------------------------------Approval flow deta hai                   
setApprovalSet(Object approvalSet):----------Approval flow set karta hai
approve():------------------------------------Request approve karta hai
reject():--------------------------------------Request reject karta hai

🔥 6️⃣ Date Methods:-
Method	                       Kya karta hai
getCreatedDate():-------------Kab request bani
setCreatedDate(Date date):----Created date set karta hai
getCompletedDate():------------Kab complete hui
setCompletedDate(Date date):---Completed date set karta hai

🔥 7️⃣ Comments / Metadata:-
Method	                       Kya karta hai
getComments():----------------Comments deta hai
setComments(String comments):-Comments set karta hai
getPriority():-----------------Priority deta hai
setPriority(String priority):--Priority set karta hai

🔥 8️⃣ Utility Methods:-
Method	                  Kya karta hai
toString():----------Object ko readable string me convert karta hai
equals(Object obj):--Compare karta hai do objects ko
hashCode():----------Hash value generate karta hai
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 1️⃣ getRequestedItems() kya karta hai?
👉 Simple Meaning:-
Ye method batata hai ki user ne kya-kya access maanga hai

📦 Iske andar kya hota hai?
Ye usually ek List return karta hai jisme har item ek request hota hai:-
Role request
Entitlement request
Account create / delete request

✅ Example:-
List items = req.getRequestedItems();
System.out.println(items);

📤 Output (example):-
[Role: Admin, Entitlement: SAP_WRITE, Account: AD_CREATE]

🔥 Real Flow:-
👉 User bolta hai:-
“Mujhe Admin role chahiye”
“Mujhe SAP write access chahiye”
➡ Ye sab items ban ke requestedItems me store ho jata hai.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ getApprovalSet() kya karta hai?
👉 Simple Meaning:-
Ye method batata hai ki request ko approve kaun karega aur kaise karega

📦 Iske andar kya hota hai?
Ye ek ApprovalSet object return karta hai jisme hota hai:-
Approvers (Manager, Admin)
Approval steps
Status (Pending / Approved / Rejected)
✅ Example:-
ApprovalSet approval = req.getApprovalSet();
System.out.println(approval);
📤 Output (example):-
Manager Approval → Pending
Security Team → Not Started
